# {{ project_name }} Frontend

A minimal Next.js (App Router) frontend, ready to run:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

The dev server starts on http://localhost:3000. `app/page.js` is the landing
page and `app/layout.js` the root layout; extend from there (add `create-next-app`
niceties like TypeScript, ESLint, or Tailwind if you want them).

## Pointing at the Django API

Create `.env.local` in this directory:

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api
```

Use `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` as the base URL for API requests. In
development the Django API runs at http://localhost:8000.
{% if api_style in ['drf', 'both'] %}
CORS is preconfigured: `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` already allows
http://localhost:3000.
{% else %}
Note: this project was generated without a REST API (`api_style` is not
`drf`/`both`), so `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` is not configured. Add
`django-cors-headers` settings before calling Django from the browser.
{% endif %}
